culture that devalues women, dishonours women,

00:19:44.130 --> 00:19:45.560
disparages women.

00:19:45.560 --> 00:19:51.410
So what happens is we take on the exterior
culture’s point of view and we think, “Oh,

00:19:51.410 --> 00:19:59.100
we must be kind of hateable or not important
or maybe we’re not valuable.”

00:19:59.100 --> 00:20:05.110
And so we internalize the patriarchal viewpoint
and then we start hating on ourselves.

00:20:05.110 --> 00:20:08.070
So when you hate on yourself you can’t love
a sister.

00:20:08.070 --> 00:20:16.290
It can only happen if you take that radical
and revolutionary step of standing for your

00:20:16.290 --> 00:20:19.800
own pleasure, which leads to self love.

00:20:19.800 --> 00:20:24.360
Because if you decide that you are important
enough to have flowers by your side one day,

00:20:24.360 --> 00:20:30.860
then that… that is an act that takes so
much courage to say, “Ok, I know I have

00:20:30.860 --> 00:20:35.730
no time, but I’m going to that flower store
and I’m putting flowers on my desk and I

00:20:35.730 --> 00:20:37.050
am worth that.”

00:20:37.050 --> 00:20:40.870
And then you do that and then suddenly you
are filled with a sense of self love.

00:20:40.870 --> 00:20:46.640
And as soon as you’re filled with love,
like feeling that way about yourself, you

00:20:46.640 --> 00:20:48.480
